Here's a complete workflow to test searching for documents with empty sources in OpenSearch Dashboard's Dev Tools:

## 1. Create a Test Index

```
PUT /test_empty_docs
{
  "mappings": {
    "properties": {
      "title": { "type": "text" },
      "content": { "type": "text" }
    }
  }
}
```

## 2. Insert Test Documents

```
# Document with normal content
POST /test_empty_docs/_doc/1
{
  "title": "Normal Document",
  "content": "This document has content"
}

# Document with partial content
POST /test_empty_docs/_doc/2
{
  "title": "Partial Document"
}

# Completely empty document
POST /test_empty_docs/_doc/3
{}

# Another normal document
POST /test_empty_docs/_doc/4
{
  "title": "Another normal",
  "content": "More content here"
}

# Another empty document
POST /test_empty_docs/_doc/5
{}
```

## 3. Refresh the Index to Make Documents Searchable

```
POST /test_empty_docs/_refresh
```

## 4. Search for Empty Documents Using Script Query

```
GET /test_empty_docs/_search
{
  "query": {
    "script": {
      "script": {
        "source": "doc['_source'].size() == 0 || doc['_source'].toString() == '{}'",
        "lang": "painless"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

## 5. Alternative Search Approach

```
GET /test_empty_docs/_search
