# Finding Empty Documents in OpenSearch - Simplified Approach

You're encountering a script error because of how we're trying to access the `_source`. Let's try simpler approaches that will reliably work in OpenSearch.

## Approach 1: Check for Absence of All Known Fields

```
GET /test_empty_docs/_search
{
  "query": {
    "bool": {
      "must_not": [
        {
          "exists": {
            "field": "title"
          }
        },
        {
          "exists": {
            "field": "content"
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  }
}
```

This query looks for documents that have neither a "title" nor "content" field, which should identify your empty documents.

## Approach 2: Create a Test Field and Check for Document Size

First, update your empty docs to include a flag:

```
POST /test_empty_docs/_update_by_query
{
  "script": {
    "source": "if (ctx._source.entrySet().size() == 0) { ctx._source.is_empty = true; } else { ctx._source.is_empty = false; }"
  }
}
```

Then query for it:

```
GET /test_empty_docs/_search
{
  "query": {
    "term": {
      "is_empty": true
    }
  }
}
```

## Approach 3: Count Fields with a Single Script Field

```
GET /test_empty_docs/_search
{
  "query": {
    "match_all": {}
  },
  "script_fields": {
    "field_count": {
      "script": {
        "source": "return params['_source'].size()"
      }
    }
  },
  "_source": true
}
```

Then look for documents where the "field_count" value is 0.

## Approach 4: Specific Object Properties Check

```
GET /test_empty_docs/_search
{
  "query": {
    "script": {
      "script": {
        "source": "return params._source.entrySet().isEmpty()",
        "lang": "painless"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

